	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><br /><strong>Utility</strong></p><ul><li><p>Each target transforms into a Large or smaller &amp;reference[beast] with a Challenge Rating of 4 or lower. You may choose a different form for each creature. The creature's equipment melds into the new form. It cannot activate, wield, or benefit from its equipment while transformed.</p></li><li><p>The transformation lasts until the spell ends, or until a creature drops to 0 hit points or dies.</p></li><li><p>The creature's game statistics are replaced by those of the new form, but it retains its alignment and &amp;reference[Intelligence], &amp;reference[Wisdom], and &amp;reference[Charisma].</p></li><li><p>The creature assumes the hit points of the new form. When it reverts, it returns to the hit points it had before the transformation. Excess damage from dropping to 0 hit points carries over to the normal form but does not knock the creature unconscious unless reduced to 0 hit points.</p></li><li><p>The creature is limited by the nature of its new form. It cannot speak or cast spells.</p></li><li><p><strong>Concentration:</strong> You may use your Action to transform affected creatures into new &amp;reference[beast] forms.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
